               <author>Morgan, Gideon</author>
               <date when="1814-02-11">February 11, 1814</date>
               <extent>2p</extent>
               <note type="summary">This document is a letter written to Return J.
				Meigs, agent to the Cherokee, from Gideon Morgan, Colonel of Cherokee forces,
				on February 11, 1814. In the letter, Morgan asks Meigs for 200 blankets for the
				Cherokee because they are without warm clothing. Morgan says that the Cherokee
				will repay Meigs for the blankets. Morgan urges Meigs to send them before they
				leave for Fort Armstrong or else the blankets will be useless.</note>
